</div>
<div class="row justify-content-center">
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <h1 class="mb-4">About Bookshelf</h1>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body p-5">
        <h2 class="mb-4">What is Bookshelf?</h2>
        <p style="line-height: 1.9;">Bookshelf is a book discovery platform that helps readers find and explore books across a wide range of genres. Browse thousands of books, discover new authors, and read reviews from fellow book lovers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body p-5">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Data Sources</h2>
        <ul style="line-height: 2.2;">
          <li><strong>Open Library API</strong> Book and author data fetched from openlibrary.org, a free and open book cataloging platform.</li>
          <li><strong>CSV File</strong> Genre data created specifically for Bookshelf, including names and descriptions for each genre.</li>
          <li><strong>Faker Gem</strong> Simulated review data including reviewer names, review bodies, and ratings.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body p-5">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Database Structure</h2>
        <ul style="line-height: 2.2;">
          <li><strong>Books</strong> Book listings with title, description, cover image, published year, pages, and rating</li>
          <li><strong>Authors</strong> Author information including name, bio, and nationality</li>
          <li><strong>Genres</strong> Book categories with names and descriptions</li>
          <li><strong>Reviews</strong> Reader reviews with reviewer name, body, and rating</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>